    <main class="u-spacing-container-xxxl">
      <section class="o-container c-intro u-spacing-container-m">
        <h2 class="c-intro__title">Develope outstanding design systems</h2>
        <p class="c-intro__body"><b>avalanche</b> establishes the foundation for a <strong>package based</strong> CSS workflow. Heavy wheight CSS toolkits often stay in your way when creating unique looking experiences or they lead to a rather bland design. But you don't have to reinvent the wheel for every new project either. <b>avalanche</b> provides building blocks for you to handpick and integrate in your workflow.</p>
      </section>

      <section class="c-section o-container u-spacing-container-m">
        <h2 class="c-section__title">Getting started</h2>
        <p><b>avalanche</b> comes with a CLI to kickstart new projects:</p>
        <pre class="c-highlight"><code class="lang-bash"><span class="c-highlight__comment"># Install the avalanche CLI.</span>
        npm install avalanchesass-cli -g
        <span class="c-highlight__comment"># Create a new project in the directory "your-project".</span>
        avalanchesass "your-project"</code></pre>
        <p><b>avalanche</b> is flexible in the way how it can be used - it is also very easy to integrate <b>avalanche</b> packages into your existing project.</p>
        <a href="/getting-started" class="c-anchor u-display-inline-block">Learn more about how to use <b>avalanche</b></a>
      </section>

